Key Match Events: Brice Sensabaugh led the Jazz to victory with a game-high 27 points, including going 5-of-6 from 3-point range.
The Jazz won against the Orlando Magic with a score of 105-92.
Pre-Game Insights: The Jazz went into the game with an extended injury report, including Lauri Markkanen, Jordan Clarkson, Keyonte George, and John Collins.
Post-Match Reflections: Jazz head coach Will Hardy expressed happiness for Brice Sensabaugh's performance, especially since he is from Orlando.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz improved to 9-25 on the season with their win over the Magic.
The Magic have been dealing with significant injuries to key players like Paulo Banchero, Franz Wagner, Moe Wagner, and Jalen Suggs.
